  "prompt": "Are Audi parts expensive?",
  "response": "Generally, Audi parts are considered more expensive compared to parts for many other car brands. This is due to several factors:\n\n1. High-quality German engineering\n2. Specialized manufacturing\n3. Complex technology\n4. Premium brand status\n5. Precise engineering tolerances\n\nSpecific reasons for higher costs include:\n- Precision-engineered components\n- Advanced technology\n- Limited availability\n- Higher labor costs for specialized repairs\n- Original equipment manufacturer (OEM) parts\n\nCompared to brands like Toyota or Honda, Audi parts can be significantly more expensive. Maintenance and repair costs are typically higher, which is an important consideration for potential Audi owners.\n\nTo manage costs, some owners:\n- Use aftermarket parts\n- Shop around for competitive prices\n- Perform basic maintenance themselves\n- Look for certified independent mechanics\n\nWhile parts are expensive, many Audi owners find the car's performance, design, and driving experience worth the additional maintenance costs.",
